      "solution": "line = input()\na, op, b = line.split()\nans = eval(line)\nif op in \"+-*\":\n    # the operator is on the same line as b, so it's len(b) + 1\n    length = max(len(str(ans)), len(a), len(b) + 1)\n    print(f\"{a:>{length}}\")\n    print(f\"{op}{b:>{length - 1}}\")\n    print(\"-\" * length)\n    print(f\"{ans:>{length}}\")\nelse:\n    a_binary = f\"{int(a):b}\"\n    b_binary = f\"{int(b):b}\"\n    ans_binary = f\"{ans:b}\"\n    length = max(len(a_binary), len(b_binary) + 1, len(ans_binary))\n    print(f\"{a_binary:>{length}}\")\n    print(f\"{op}{b_binary:>{length - 1}}\")\n    print(\"-\" * length)\n    print(f\"{ans_binary:>{length}}\")\n",
